LangGraph::
        an open-source Python library developed by LangChain, designed to build stateful, 
        multi-actor applications with Large Language Models (LLMs) by modeling workflows as graphs
        It enables building complex, agent-like behaviors by introducing cycles, looping, and conditional branching to LLM application

In simple words, 
         it is an orchestration layer, specifically designed as a low-level orchestration framework and runtime for building,
          managing, and deploying stateful, multi-agent AI applications.

it is a middleware that automates the workflow,nodes,services for a complex task with memory
whereas in langchain it is statelss(memory isnt internal) but this is stateful
it contains nodes,workflows,edges,loops,feedback cycles,control used to build ,maintain and manage the agent works

Agent : a system or program that is capable of autonomously performing tasks on behalf of a user or another system.
it uses tools and manage maintain the tasks tom complete 

Agents need reliabilty , but for complex info and memory connections we use langgraph 


nodes                      functions
edges                      connections
directed graphs            the pointing direction
cyclic graphs               start and end are same
DAGs                       direction and acyclic
transitions                the movement from one to other node
entry_point                 the start point
end_point                   END


State = shared memory flowing through graph.
Routers = Functions deciding next node.
